The '''Food Act 1981''' is a current Act of Parliament in [[New Zealand]]. It is administered by the [[Ministry for Primary Industries (New Zealand)|Ministry for Primary Industries]].

The [[Food Act 2014]] will replace the Food Act progressively over three years from when it comes into force in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foodsafety.govt.nz/policy-law/food-act-2014/overview.htm|title=Overview <U+2013> Food Act 2014|publisher=Ministry for Primary Industries|accessdate=21 February 2015}}</ref>

